---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Learn about Cassie, a community-focused CPR and first aid trainer."
	pubDate={new Date('2026-03-17')}
	heroImage="/cassie.jpg"
>
	<p>
		Hi, I’m Cassie (She/They). I run Cassie's Practice Resuscitation Training,
		focused on making CPR and first aid training accessible for everyone. I offer a range of
		sessions—from assessment-only training for those wanting to renew their certificate, to
		in-depth training for anyone wanting extra hands-on practice and
		confidence.
	</p>

	<p>
		My goal is simple: to give people the practical skills and confidence they need to respond
		in an emergency, without the barriers of high costs or intimidating classroom settings.
		All sessions are low-cost or pay-what-you-can, and I tailor training for individuals and community groups.
	</p>
	<p>
		My experience spans healthcare, outdoor education, and emergency response. I have worked
		as a first aid trainer, ski and mountain bike patrol member, and in outdoor educator. This diverse background allows me to bring practical,
		real-world scenarios to every session.
	</p>
	<h2>My Values</h2>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> I strive to make training affordable and welcoming.</li>
		<li><strong>Practicality:</strong> Hands-on, realistic sessions that build muscle memory.</li>
		<li><strong>Community:</strong> Supporting local groups and those with limited access to training.</li>
	</ul>


	<p>
		If you’d like me to run a session for you, your workplace, or community group, please
		<a href="/contact">get in touch</a>.
	</p>
</Layout>